fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.mapreduce

Interface ProcessorI<R>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<ContentDataI,R>, java.io.Serializable
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ProcessorI<R>
extends java.util.function.Function<ContentDataI,R>, java.io.Serializable
    The functional interface ProcessorI allows to define functions in the map part of the map/reduce protocol that process individual data of type ContentDataI to produce individual results of type R.

    Description

    In the map part of the map/reduce, each data must be individually processed to produce individual results that will be combined in the reduce part. The processor functions in this DHT/MapReduce project must implement ProcessorI<R>, which is a specialisation of the Java functional interface Function<ContentDataI,R> that takes a parameter that is a data contained in the DHT and returns a result of type R to be defined.

    The ProcessorI<R> functional interface is itself serialisable as in a DHT, they have to be passed as parameters over the network.
